<journalOrPublisher id="2E2F41E5D964BB07FBF7F879622C684D" jopScore="0.21433462" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">Lu (1992: 331) in sharing small pseudobulbs, ovoid oblong leaves, and margin fimbriate-ciliate dorsal sepal, but can be distinguished from it by having longer scape, short and straight side lateral sepals, ovate-triangular petals and ligulate lip</journalOrPublisher>
.
